definitions.definition: The number of elements a given set contains.
examples: The empty set has a cardinality of zero.

definitions.definition: The number of terms that can inhabit a type ; the possible values of a type.
The property of a relationship between a database table and another one, specifying whether it is one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-one, or many-to-many.

main_definition: ( set theory , of a set ) The number of elements a given set contains.
